ary%206%2C%202021%2C%20attack%20on%20the%20US%20Capitol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20question%20of%20his%20age%20always%20loomed%20large.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20eventually%20joked%20about%20it%20but%20always%20denied%20it%20was%20an%20issue%2C%20even%20after%20a%20debate%20where%20his%20rambling%20answers%20and%20listless%20stare%20sparked%20a%20revolt%20by%20Democrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20mix%20of%20pride%20and%20his%20conviction%20that%20Trump%20was%20a%20threat%20to%20democracy%20kept%20Biden%20fighting%20until%20it%20was%2C%20perhaps%2C%20too%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFranklin%20Foer%2C%20author%20of%20a%20book%20on%20the%20Biden%20presidency%2C%20wrote%20recently%20that%20%26quot%3Bhumiliation%20--%20and%20its%20transcendence%20--%20is%20Biden's%20origin%20story.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRight%20now%20it%20is%20his%20psychological%20prison%2C%20a%20mental%20habit%20that%20might%20doom%20American%20democracy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20the%20Atlantic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Cruel%20losses'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20outlook%20was%20largely%20formed%20by%20a%20hardscrabble%20childhood%20in%20Scranton%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20in%20the%20American%20rust-belt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20was%20part%20of%20a%20close-knit%20Irish%20Catholic%20family%20--%20he%20was%20just%20the%20second%20Catholic%20US%20president%20after%20his%20hero%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20--%20that%20was%20known%20for%20its%20intense%20pride.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20mother%20Jean%20told%20the%20young%20Joey%20and%20his%20siblings%20every%20day%20that%20%26quot%3Bnobody%20was%20better%20than%20a%20Biden%2C%26quot%3B%20Ben%20Cramer%20wrote%20in%20his%20book%20%26quot%3BWhat%20It%20Takes%2C%26quot%3B%20about%20the%201988%20US%20election%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20also%20known%20for%20never%20backing%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20decided%20to%20fight...%20BANGO%20--%20he'd%20punch%20the%20guy%20in%20the%20face%2C%2