nutes%20later%20with%20an%20expression%20of%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EMy%20fellow%20Democrats%2C%20I%20have%20decided%20not%20to%20accept%20the%20nomination%20and%20to%20focus%20all%20my%20energies%20on%20my%20duties%20as%20President%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20my%20term.%20My%20very%20first%20decision%20as%20the%20party%20nominee%20in%202020%20was%20to%20pick%20Kamala%20Harris%20as%20my%20Vice%20President.%20And%20it's%20been%20the%20best%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fx8DnvuImJV%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2Fx8DnvuImJV%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Joe%20Biden%20(%40JoeBiden)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJoeBiden%2Fstatus%2F1815087772216303933%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2021%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%2C%2059%2C%20would%20become%20the%20first%20Black%20woman%20to%20do%20run%20at%20the%20top%20of%20a%20major-party%20ticket%20in%20the%20country's%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20unclear%20whether%20other%20senior%20Democrats%20would%20challenge%20Harris%20for%20the%20party's%20nomination%20-%20she%20was%20widely%20seen%20as%20the%20pick%20for%20many%20party%20officials%20-%20or%20whether%20the%20party%20itself%20would%20choose%20to%20open%20the%20field%20for%20nominations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden's%20announcement%20follows%20a%20wave%20of%20public%20and%20private%20pressure%20from%20Democratic%20lawmakers%20and%20party%20officials%20to%20quit%20the%20race%20after%20his%20shockingly%20poor%20performance%20in%20a%20June%2027%20televised%20debate%20last%20month%20against%20Republican%20rival%20Trump%2C%2078.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden's%20failure%20at%20times%20to%20complete%20clear%20sentences%20took%20the%20public%20spotlight%20away%20from%20Trump's%20performance%2C%20in%20which%20he%20made%20a%20string%20of%20false%20statements%2C%20and%20trained%20it%20instead%20on%20questions%20surrounding%20Biden's%20fitness%20for%20another%204-year%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDays%20later%20he%20raised%20fresh%20concerns%20in%20an%20interview%2C%20shrugging%20off%20Democrats'%20worries%20and%20a%20widening%20gap%20in%20opinion%20polls%2C%20and%20saying%20he%20would%20be%20fine%20losing%20to%20Trump%20if%20he%20knew%20he'd%20%26quot%3Bgave%20it%20my%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20gaffes%20at%20a%20NATO%20summit%20-%20invoking%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20name%20when%20he%20meant%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskiy%20and%20calling%20Harris%20%26quot%3BVice%20President%20Trump%26quot%3B%20-further%20stoked%20anxieties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20four%20days%20before%20Sunday's%20announcement%2C%20Biden%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20COVID-19%20for%20a%20third%20time%2C%20forcing%20him%20to%20cut%20short%20a%20campaign%20trip%20to%20Las%20Vegas.%20More%20than%20one%20in%2010%20congressional%20Democrats%20had%20called%20publicly%20for%20him%20to%20quit%20the%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden's%20historic%20move%20-%20the%20first%20sitting%20president%20to%20give%20up%20his%20party's%20nomination%20for%20reelection%20since%20President%20Lyndon%20Johnson%20in%20March%201968%20-%20leaves%20his%20replacement%20with%20less%20than%20four%20months%20to%20wage%20a%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Harris%20emerges%20as%20the%20nominee%2C%20the%20move%20would%20represent%20an%20unprecedented%20gamble%20by%20the%20Democratic%20Party%3A%20its%20first%20Black%20and%20Asian%20American%20woman%20to%20run%20for%20the%20White%20House%20in%20a%20country%20that%20has%20elected%20one%20Black%20president%20and%20never%20a%20woman%20president%20in%20more%20than%20two%20centuries%20of%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20was%20the%20oldest%20U.S.%20president%20ever%20elected%20when%20he%20beat%20Trump%20in%202020.%20During%20that%20campaign%2C%20Biden%20described%20himself%20as%20a%20bridge%20to%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20Democratic%20leaders.%20Some%20interpreted%20that%20to%20mean%20he%20would%20serve%20one%20term%2C%20a%20transitional%20figure%20who%20beat%20Trump%20and%20brought%20his%20party%20back%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20set%20his%20sights%20on%20a%20second%20term%20in%20the%20belief%20that%20he%20was%20the%20only%20Democrat%20who%20could%20beat%20Trump%20again%20amid%20questions%20about%20Harris's%20experience%20and%20popularity.%20In%20recent%20times%2C%20though%2C%20his%20advanced%20age%20began%20to%20show%20through%20more.%20His%20gait%20became%20stilted%20and%20his%20childhood%20stutter%20occasionally%20returned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20team%20had%20hoped%20a%20strong%20performance%20at%20the%20June%2027%20debate%20would%20ease%20concerns%20over%20his%20age.%20It%20did%20the%20opposite%3A%20a%20Reuters%2FIpsos%20poll%20after%20the%20debate%20showed%20that%20about%2040%25%20of%20Democrats%20thought%20he%20should%20quit%20the%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDonors%20began%20to%20revolt%20and%20supporters%20of%20Harris%20began%20to%20coalesce%20around%20her.%20Top%20Democrats%2C%20including%20former%20House%20of%20Representatives%20Speaker%20Nancy%20Pelosi%2C%20a%20longtime%20ally%2C%20told%20Biden%20he%20cannot%20win%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20initially%20resisted%20pressure%20to%20step%20aside.%20He%20held%20damage-control%20calls%20and%20meetings%20with%20lawmakers%20and%20state%20governors%2C%20and%20sat%20for%20rare%20television%20interviews.%20But%20it%20was%20not%20enough.%20Polls%20showed%20Trump's%20lead%20in%20key%20battleground%20states%20widening%2C%20and%20Democrats%20began%20to%20fear%20a%20wipeout%20in%20the%20House%20and%20Senate.%20On%20July%2017%2C%20California's%20Rep.%20Adam%20Schiff%20called%20on%20him%20to%20exit%20the%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden's%20departure%20sets%20up%20a%20stark%20new%20contrast%2C%20between%20the%20Democrats'%20presumptive%20new%20nominee%2C%20Harris%2C%20a%20former%20prosecutor%2C%20and%20Trump%20who%20at%2078%20is%20two%20decades%20her%20senior%20and%20faces%20two%20outstanding%20criminal%20prosecutions%20related%20to%20his%20attempts%20to%20overturn%20the%202020%20election%20result.%20He%20is%20due%20to%20be%20sentenced%20in%20New%20York%20in%20September%20on%20a%20conviction%20for%20trying%20to%20cover%20up%20a%20hush-money%20payment%20to%20a%20porn%20star.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBIDEN%20STRUGGLED%20BEFORE%20DEBATE%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20facing%20little%20opposition%2C%20Biden%20easily%20won%20the%20Democratic%20Party's%20primary%20race%20to%20pick%20its%20presidential%20candidate%2C%20despite%20voter%20concerns%20about%20his%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20his%20staunch%20support%20for%20Israel's%20military%20campaign%20in%20Gaza%20eroded%20support%20among%20some%20in%20his%20own%20party%2C%20particularly%20young%2C%20progressive%20Democrats%20and%20voters%20of%20color.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20Black%20voters%20say%20Biden%20has%20not%20done%20enough%20for%20them%2C%20and%20enthusiasm%20among%20Democrats%20overall%20for%20a%20second%20Biden%20term%20had%20been%20low.%20Even%20before%20the%20debate%20with%20Trump%2C%20Biden%20was%20trailing%20the%20Republican%20in%20some%20national%20polls%20and%20in%20the%20battleground%20states%20he%20would%20have%20needed%20to%20win%20to%20prevail%20on%20Nov.%205.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%20was%20tasked%20with%20reaching%20out%20to%20those%20voters%20in%20recent%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20primary%20race%2C%20Biden%20accumulated%20more%20than%203%2C600%20delegates%20to%20the%20Democratic%20National%20Convention%20to%20be%20held%20in%20Chicago%20in%20August.%20That%20was%20almost%20double%20the%201%2C976%20needed%20to%20win%20the%20party's%20nomination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnless%20the%20Democratic%20Party%20changes%20the%20rules%2C%20delegates%20pledged%20to%20Biden%20would%20enter%20the%20convention%20%26quot%3Buncommitted%2C%26quot%3B%20leaving%20them