pted%20the%20nomination%2C%20Spies%20wrote%20that%20Biden%20becomes%20beholden%20to%20the%20Federal%20Election%20Campaign%20Act's%20rules%20regulating%20%26quot%3Bexcess%20campaign%20funds%26quot%3B%20and%20can%20no%20longer%20donate%20more%20than%20%242%2C000%20to%20any%20other%20candidate%2C%C2%A0including%20Harris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaurav%20Ghosh%2C%20the%20director%20of%20federal%20campaign%20finance%20reform%20at%20the%20Campaign%20Legal%20Center%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2F91-million-question-what-happens-bidens-campaign-money-2024-07-18%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2C%20as%20long%20as%20Harris%20remains%20in%20the%20race%2C%20she%20automatically%20has%20access%20to%20the%20campaign's%20shared%20funds%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0regardless%20of%20whether%20the%20pair%20had%20formally%20accepted%20the%20nomination%20or%20not%2C%20since%20both%20names%20appeared%20on%20the%20same%20campaign%20registration%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Spies%20and%20Ghosh%20noted%20that%20either%20way%2C%20there%20are%20workarounds.%20The%20Biden%20campaign%20can%20either%20refund%20its%20donors%2C%20Ghosh%20told%20Reuters%2C%20or%2C%20they%20agreed%2C%20the%20campaign%20can%20direct%20the%20money%20to%20the%20Democratic%20National%20Committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDan%20McMillan%2C%20founder%20and%20executive%20director%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsavedemocracyinamerica.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESave%20Democracy%20in%20America%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20nonpartisan%20campaign%20to%20end%20the%20influence%20of%20corporate%20and%20special%20interest%20money%20in%20politics%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20it%20ultimately%20doesn't%20matter%20which%20expert%20was%20right%20about%20the%20formal%20nomination%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0Biden%20didn't%20stay%20in%20the%20race%20long%20enough%20to%20accept%20it%2C%20and%20it%20wouldn't%20have%20made%20a%20difference%20if%20he%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20challenges%20may%20arise%20over%20how%2C%20exactly%2C%20these%20types%20of%20scenarios%20should%20play%20out%2C%20but%20final%20determinations%20in%20those%20cases%20will%20ultimately%20be%20made%20long%20after%20the%20election%20is%20decided.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20a%20nonargument%20because%20that%20money%20is%20not%20going%20to%20go%20to%20waste%2C%26quot%3B%20McMillan%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIf%20someone%20other%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjoe-biden-endorses-kamala-harris-after-dropping-out-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHarris%20becomes%20the%20nominee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%20the%20campaign%20will%20just%20give%20this%20money%20to%20the%20Democratic%20National%20Committee%20or%20to%20other%20party%20committees%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20those%20committees%20can%20then%20spend%20that%20money%20in%20ways%20that%20benefit%20the%20presidential%20campaign%20of%20other%20Democratic%20candidates.%20So%20the%20money's%20not%20going%20to%20go%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20funds%20are%20ultimately%20transferred%20to%20the%20Democratic%20National%20Committee%2C%20the%20party%20can%20then%20spend%20unlimited%20amounts%20on%20ads%20promoting%20a%20new%20candidate%20and%20up%20to%20%2432%20million%20directly%20on%20a%20new%20campaign.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20funds%20can%20be%20divvied%20up%20to%20other%20other%20action%20committees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhoever%20ends%20up%20as%20the%20Democratic%20nominee%2C%20McMillan%20noted%2C%20they'll%20have%20no%20shortage%20of%20financial%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20gonna%20make%20a%20huge%20difference%20in%20how%20the%20campaign%20is%20conducted%20in%20a%20meaningful%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20McMillan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjoe-biden-campaign-funds-after-he-dropped-out-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%