0groundwater%20and%20supply%20water%20to%20nearby%20rural%20development%20blocks%20and%20%3Cem%3Egram%20panchayats%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20will%20take%20us%20three%20more%20months%20to%20complete%20this%20project%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Himanshu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20the%20multi-pronged%20approach%2C%20Himanshu%20says%20the%20water%20table%20in%20the%20region%20has%20improved.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20our%20water%20table%20has%20increased%20from%200.8%20to%201%20metre.%20One%20of%20the%20blocks%20in%20Varanasi%2C%20Pindra%2C%20has%20come%20out%20of%20the%20dark%20status%2C%20which%20is%20given%20to%20a%20block%20with%20extremely%20poor%20groundwater%20levels.%20In%20Pindra%2C%20water%20had%20reduced%20to%20an%20extent%20that%20we%20had%20to%20ban%20any%20kind%20of%20groundwater%20extraction.%20There%2C%20we%20have%20observed%20an%20increase%20of%201.7%20metres%20in%20the%20water%20table%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20revival%20of%20the%20Nad%20river%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20holistic%20approach%20towards%20groundwater%20recharge%2C%20the%20IAS%20officer%20estimates%20to%20have%20spent%20Rs%2080%20crore%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years.%20He%20urges%20citizens%20to%20be%20cognisant%20of%20the%20water%20scarcity%20in%20the%20country%20and%20be%20actively%20involved%20in%20water%20conservation%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20open%20our%20taps%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20never-ending%20resource%20but%20that%20is%20not%20the%20case.%20Think%20of%20the%20person%20in%20a%20rural%20area%20living%20in%20a%20faraway%20hinterland%20who%20has%20to%20walk%20miles%20to%20fetch%20water.%20Being%20responsible%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F347615%2Fbengaluru-water-crisis-measures-to-save-water-at-home-greywater-rainwater-odette-katrak-designs-ecowaternomics-framework%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eutilising%20water%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecould%20lead%20to%20a%20big%20impact%20on%20their%20lives.%20We%20should%20leave%20a%20sustainable%20ecosystem%20where%20kids%20have%20ample%20amounts%20of%20water%20in%20the%20future%20because%20no%20life%20is%20possible%20without%20water%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3B%20All%20photos%3A%20Himanshu%20Nagpal.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721299593000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fvaranasi-1721270245.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D357468%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22IAS%20officer%20Himanshu%20Nagpal%2C%20the%20chief%20development%20officer%20in%20Varanasi%2C%20initiated%20a%20comprehensive%20groundwater%20rejuvenation%20project%2C%20notably%20increasing%20the%20water%20table%2C%20improving%20water%20availability%20and%20reducing%20waterborne%20diseases.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20how%20he%20achieved%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F357468%2Fias-officer-revive-water-table-cdo-varanasi-himanshu-nagpal-rainwater-harvesting-river-rejuvenation-groundwater-recharge%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%225%20Farmers%20Who%20Switched%20to%20Hydroponics%20%26amp%3B%20Turned%20Their%20Lives%20Around%20With%20Better%20Profits%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20conversation%20with%20an%20engineer-turned-farmer%20and%20co-founder%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fs%3DEeki%2Bfoods%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAbhay%20Singh%20of%20Eeki%20Foods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20what%20fascinated%20me%20the%20most%20was%20the%20evolution%20of%20farming.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20no%20background%20in%20the%20field%20whatsoever%2C%20I%20only%20had%20a%20layman%E2%80%99s%20knowledge%20of%20how%20my%20food%20was%20gro